    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix use-after-free vulnerability in LTE Viterbi decoder test function\n\n### Summary\nThe `test_viterbi` function in the LTE Viterbi decoder had two critical issues that could lead to undefined behavior and potential security vulnerabilities:\n\n1. The function was declared to return an `int` but failed to return any value, causing undefined behavior when the return value was used by the calling code.\n\n2. A more serious use-after-free vulnerability existed in the `phy_viterbi_lte_sse2` function where a static pointer `TB_ptr2` retained references to stack-allocated memory after the function returned. This could cause memory corruption if the function was called reentrantly or in multithreaded contexts.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/viterbi_lte.c`: \n  - Added missing return statement in `test_viterbi` function\n  - Changed `static uint8_t *TB_ptr2` to `uint8_t *TB_ptr2` in `phy_viterbi_lte_sse2` to eliminate use-after-free vulnerability\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Compile the code with TEST_DEBUG flag enabled\n2. Run the test_viterbi function in a multithreaded environment or call it reentrantly\n3. Observe potential segmentation faults or memory corruption due to the static pointer referencing freed stack memory\n\nThe fix ensures proper function return values and eliminates the use-after-free condition by making the pointer local to the function scope.\n"
}